        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 18 at 1:05PM CDT by NWS Lake Charles LA</headline>
        <description>At 105 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Ridge, or near Scott, moving east at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to vegetation and outdoor
objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lafayette, Scott, Carencro, Broussard, Youngsville, Duson, Maurice,
Ridge, and Milton.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
